default1.1.
default&#xa0; 
defaultWildlife and Countryside Link (Link) brings together 42 voluntary organisations concerned with the conservation and protection of wildlife, countryside and the marine environment. Our members practise and advocate environmentally sensitive land management, and encourage respect for and enjoyment of natural landscapes and features, the historic and marine environment and biodiversity. Taken together
default,
default our members have the support of over eight million people in the UK and manage over 690,000 hectares of land.
default&#xa0;default1.2.
default&#xa0; 
defaultLink convened a dedicated Task and Finish Group to work on Invasive Non-Native Species 
default(INNS) 
defaultissues in late 2012, which brings 
defaulttogether 
defaultconsiderable scientific, policy and practical experience of issues relating to INNS. Our objectives include scrutinising government policy, gathering evidence on the impacts of INNS on the third sector, and raising the profile of the issue with government and the public alike. Our preliminary analysis
default, developed in early 2013,
default of the fitness and success of 
defaultT
defaulthe
default 
defaultInvasive Non-native Species Framework Strategy for Great Britain
default 
default(‘
defaultGB 
defaultS
defaulttrategy
default’)
default was presented to the then Minister for Biodiversity, the Rt Hon Richard Benyon MP. We welcome the subsequent commitment from Defra to undertake not a ‘light touch’ review, but one that appears to be thorough and inclusive. 
